ized with "difference of opinion." Using a multidimensional perspective this book explores whether black racial identity differences among blacks influence political attitudes and behavior.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitics and government. 0aAfrican AmericansxRace identity. 0aAfrican AmericansxSocial conditions. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPsychology : Psychology. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh1 aCross, William E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWinburn, Jonathan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2018z978311149142440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438471624423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438471624/original  a978-3-11-149142-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles